; ---- World root — floor chunks + seam markers spawned at runtime ----
; ProcgenSpike.gd's _ready() loads the worked-example ZoneDef, runs
; FloorAssembler.assemble_floor(...), and spawns ColorRect floor +
; Label + 2-px seam-marker nodes under this World. The hand-stitched
; ColorRects from the camera-scroll spike are intentionally not
; replicated here — the placement IS the proof; we render what the
; assembler produces.

[node name="World" type="Node2D" parent="."]

; ---- Marker (the camera's follow target) ----
; Same shape as the camera-scroll spike: CharacterBody2D + 12×16
; ember-orange Sprite ColorRect. WASD via the production move_*
; InputMap. ProcgenSpike.gd repositions the marker to the entry
; anchor's left-quarter in _ready (so the marker doesn't spawn off the
; rendered floor).

